<h1>Getting Started in Syrnia</h1>
Hello and welcome to Syrnia! This guide will get you up and running with the basics of game play  in no time! Once you finish the tutorial island you will find yourself in Sanfew. The only things  you'll find here are the island of Remer's Jail and a few player made shops. So the first thing  you will want to do is move to another city.  <br />
<br />
To move to from Sanfew look at the mini-map in the top right of the playing screen and click on  the dot next to Rynir Mines. While you wait for the timer to count down we'll take a look at  the rest of the play screen.  <br />
<h3>Inventory</h3>
To the top-left of your screen is your inventory. These are the items you have in your  possession. You begin the game with the following: Beginners horse, a Bronze Dagger, a Bronze  Pickaxe, a Hammer, a Net, a Tinderbox, and a Bronze Hatchet. When you click these items, you  will equip/un-equip/use/eat them. <br />
<br />
<h3>The Buttons</h3>
Just below your inventory is some buttons. <br />
<br />
These are, in order: <br />
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Options</span> - to change your password.  <br />
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Messages</span> - Where you can send and receive secure  messages to fellow players or game staff. To contact game staff, open the Messages tab, and select &quot;<em>Contact the game staff, use the ticket system</em>&quot;. Give the ticket a title, select which category it goes to and tell us what the problem is. Then decide how you want us to contact you. If you choose to have us email you with a response, you must provide a valid email.<br />
<br />
Or you can also use this:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.syrnia.com/tickets.php"><em>&quot;Send a ticket to game staff&quot;</em></a><br />
<br />
<u>Departments:<br />
</u>
<ul>
    <li>Chat - If you have a question about chat channels or wish to report a chat violation.</li>
    <li>Forum - Any questions regarding forums or to report forum violations.</li>
    <li>Multi/Cheat/Exploit - If you suspect someone to be cheating, this is who you speak to.</li>
    <li>Bugs - If you find a fault with the game, speak to these mods.</li>
    <li>Registration/Game information - If you have problems starting your game account or general questions, ask these mods.</li>
    <li>Premium points - Any questions regarding Syrnia premium points.</li>
</ul>
Note: If you are submitting a complaint to a member of staff, you must enclose evidence. Acceptable evidence can be in the form of a chat log showing the incident, a copy of a forum thread or link to forum thread, or a full message (must have timestamp and title).<font class="ModChat"><br />
<br />
</font><span style="font-weight: bold;">Quests </span>- Quests and Jobs you are currently doing will  be displayed in here.  More information is available on the <a href="http://www.syrnia.com/index.php?page=manual&amp;m=quests">Quests</a> page.<br />
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Forum</span> - is where you can post messages that everyone can  see. Good sections to take a look at when your just starting out are the general, help and clan topics.  <br />
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Clan</span> - Where you can join or create a clan. Once you're  in a clan you can post messages for your clan mates to read in the forum, see on the news page  important information posted by the clan leader, and see who is online and where they are in Syrnia on the member list.  <br />
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold;">Logout</span> - is for logging out when you're done playing. <br />
<br />
<h3>What you're wearing </h3>
Below the buttons you will see what looks like a cut out of a person. This represents what  armor/weapons you are wearing. If you click the Bronze Dagger in you inventory, you will see  it equipped as your weapon. <br />
<br />
<h3>City Menu</h3>
Just to the right of your inventory you will see a column headed &quot;City Menu&quot;. This is where you  will be able to select the various actions to do in each city.  <br />
<br />
Under the city menu, you will see a list of player names. You can click on a player name to see  what they are wearing and have an option to attempt to thieve them. Below the player list is a  dropped items section. If there is ever anything on the ground it will be displayed here and  you can choose to pick the items up.  <br />
<br />
<h3>Maps</h3>
On the right side of the screen just under the mini-map you will see a &quot;View Full World map&quot;  link. If you click on this you will see a full map of Remer Island. At the bottom of the map is  another link where you can see the world of Syrnia. From there you can click on the individual  links to see maps of all of the other islands, including Skull Island, the fabled home of the  pirates.  <br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.syrnia.com/images/worldmap.php?map=full"><em>&quot;Full Syrnia World Map&quot;</em></a><br />
<br />
<h3>Skills</h3>
If you look on the right of your screen, in the middle, you will see a picture representing  every game skill in a column. By clicking any one of these pictures you will see a pop-up  appear with the skill details for your character. There is also some facts like how long you  have been playing etc.  <br />
Syrnia has many skills you can work on. Skill building requires Experience (Exp, or &quot;xp&quot;),  which is gained every time you perform a skill. <br />
<br />
Just a little above the skill pictures you will see, from the top, your current health, your  current gold (GP) then the total of your skill levels, your combat level (CL, is a combination of your health, strength, attack and defense levels,) and the last is your fame.  Fame is gained by being one of the top three fighters to prevent the pirates from capturing a  town, or you can gain negative fame by becoming a pirate and donating resources to the pirate  stockpile and when a city is successfully captured during an invasion.)  <br />
<br />
<h3>Chat</h3>
At the bottom of the screen is the chat window where you can talk to everyone that plays Syrnia. There are five chat channels in Syrnia, each with its own purpose.  <br />
<br />
